**Key question: Why is keeping an OS patched and up-to-date important?**

Keeping an operating system updated is critical for security and performance. Updates fix known security vulnerabilities before attackers can exploit them, protect against newly discovered threats, patch bugs that could cause instability, and often include performance improvements. An unpatched OS is one of the most common and preventable attack vectors.

